rewards.description: A phantasmal gem formed inside the tissue of Xeno'jiiva. The power it holds defies comprehension.

rewards.name: Xeno'jiiva Ticket
rewards.description: A ticket bearing Xeno'jiiva, elder dragon transcended. Redeem at the Smithy to make novel equipment.

name: Zorah Magdaros
description: An elder dragon that rises from the earth like a volcano. Where it's headed, and why, the Research Commission has yet to figure out.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Heat Scale
rewards.description: Zorah Magdaros material. Mostly obtained as a reward. Broadly used for many purposes.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Carapace
rewards.description: Zorah Magdaros material. Obtained as a rare drop or by mining. Solid, used to craft gear.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Ridge
rewards.description: Zorah Magdaros material. Mostly obtained as a reward. Stout, used in many weapons.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Pleura
rewards.description: Zorah Magdaros material. Obtained by breaking its chest. Heavy, used to craft armor.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Magma
rewards.description: Zorah Magdaros material. Obtained by breaking its head. Unusual and difficult to handle.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Gem
rewards.description: A rare gem said to have formed with Zorah Magdaros tissue. Holds untold potential.

rewards.name: Zorah Magdaros Ticket
rewards.description: A ticket bearing Zorah, trampling over the New World. Redeem at the Smithy to make novel equipment.

name: Leshen
description: Dwelling deep inside the forest, these creatures use their innate magic to control all flora and fauna within their territory.

rewards.name: Ancient Leshen Skull
rewards.description: Rare ancient leshen material. Embued with powerful magic and harboring unfathomable darkness.

rewards.name: Leshen Skull
rewards.description: Proof of defeating a leshen. In another world, hunters hang this from their horse saddle to show off.

rewards.name: Cursed Bone
rewards.description: Rare material. The bone of a creature that fell prey to a leshen's cunning cruelty.

rewards.name: Leshen Antlers
rewards.description: Rare material. The horrifying antlers of a leshen, nourished by the innate powers of primeval woods.

rewards.name: Leshen Claw
rewards.description: A rare sharp leshen claw. One hit is enough to leave a deep gash on its victim.

rewards.name: Leshen Resin
rewards.description: A lump of resin excreted by the leshen. Contains arcane components that should be handled with care.

name: Ancient Leshen
description: An old leshen that arrived through a portal to assume control over the Ancient Forest. Sometimes revered as an indigenous deity.

rewards.name: Ancient Leshen Skull
rewards.description: Rare ancient leshen material. Embued with powerful magic and harboring unfathomable darkness.

rewards.name: Ancient Cursed Bone
rewards.description: Rare ancient leshen material. A bone entangled in countless magical branches.

rewards.name: Ancient Leshen Antlers
rewards.description: Rare ancient leshen material. Huge, solemn antlers that inspire fear in other creatures.

rewards.name: Ancient Leshen Claw
rewards.description: Rare material. The claw of an ancient leshen, worshipped as an indigenous god in another world.

name: Safi'jiiva
description: The fully-grown form of Xeno'jiiva. It absorbs energy from its environment to heal itself and change the ecosystem.

rewards.name: Safi'jiiva Hardhorn
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Obtained by breaking its horns. Excessive growth has caused the horns to curl.

rewards.name: Safi'jiiva Shard
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Mostly obtained by carving. Its maturation has caused patterns to appear.

rewards.name: Safi'jiiva Fellwing
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Obtained by breaking its wings. Feel the oppressive power of the emperor.

rewards.name: Zionium Crystal
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. The grand energy of the descended emperor lies within its core.

rewards.name: Safi'jiiva Cortex
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Mostly obtainend as a reward. Its maturatioon has created complex layers to appear.

rewards.name: Safi'jiiva Hardclaw
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Obtained by breaking its legs. Touch them to feel the torrent of the earth below.

rewards.name: Pulsing Dragonshell
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Eternal time, along with its inherent power has caused brilliant light to seep out.

rewards.name: Safi'jiiva Lash
rewards.description: Very rare Safi'jiiva material. Obtained by carving its severed tail. A single swipe is said to cause cyclones.

name: Stygian Zinogre
description: Has a symbiotic relationship with Dracophage Bugs, which it releases like bullets. Becomes even more dangerous when covered in light.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre Dragonhold
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Mostly obtained by carving. Compatible with dragon element.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre  Skymerald
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Used to craft weapons powerful enough to take over the world.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre Hardclaw
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Obtained by breaking its forelegs. Sharp, used in many weapons.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre Dragonlocks
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Mostly obtained as a reward. Solid, used to craft gear.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre Hardhorn
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Obtained by breaking its head. Stout, used in many weapons.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre Cortex
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Mostly obtained as a reward. Solid, used to craft gear.

rewards.name: Dracophage Bug
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Can be gathered when it's toppled. Grants dragon element properties.

rewards.name: Stygian Zinogre Lash
rewards.description: Very rare Stygian Zinogre material. Obtained by carving its severed tail. Stiff, used to craft gear.

rewards.name: Tempered Dragonhold
rewards.description: Very rare Tempered Stygian Zinogre material. A product of the brutal power struggle in the Guiding Lands.

name: Rajang
description: An ultra-aggressive creature that few have a chance of surviving against. Sports powerful arms that pack a punch, and turns gold when angry.

rewards.name: Gold Rajang Pelt+
rewards.description: Very rare Rajang material. Hard to obtain, but greatly increases the effectiveness of equipment.

rewards.name: Rajang Hardhorn
rewards.description: Very rare Rajang material. Obtained by breaking its horns. Stout, used in many weapons.

rewards.name: Rajang Tail
rewards.description: Very Rare Rajang material. Obtained by breaking its tail. Stiff, used to craft gear.

rewards.name: Rajang Hardclaw
rewards.description: Very rare Rajang, material. Obtained by breaking its forelimbs. Sharp, used in many weapons.

rewards.name: Tempered Glimmerpelt

rewards.name: Bloodthirsty Glimmerpelt
rewards.description: Very rare Rajang material. The Guiding Lands' ebergy fortifies the monsters living there.

rewards.name: Rajang Hardfang
rewards.description: Very rare Rajang material. Mostly obtained by carving. Sharp, used in many weapons.

name: Viper Tobi-Kadachi
description: The tail of this subspecies secretes a toxin while its fangs paralyze prey. It can also glide without climbing trees.

rewards.description: Very rare Viper Tobi-Kadachi material. Obtained by breaking its forelimbs. Sharp, used in many weapons.

rewards.name: Viper Tobi-Kadachi Membrane+

rewards.name: Viper Tobi-Kadachi Shard

rewards.description: Very rare Viper Tobi-Kadachi material. The Guiding Lands' energy fortifies the monsters living there.

rewards.name: Tempered Viperthorn

name: Namielle
description: An Elder Dragon said to be able to command water and use it as a shield. Though very few sightings have ever been reported, they mention 'exploding water' and 'bright glowing lights.' Its existence remains shrouded in mystery.

rewards.name: Namielle Fellwing
rewards.description: Very rare Namielle material. Obtained by breaking its wings. Supple, used to craft gear.

rewards.name: Namielle Finehide
rewards.description: Very rare Namielle material. Mostly obtained by carving. Broadly used for many purposes.

rewards.name: Namielle Hardclaw

rewards.name: Enchanting Finehide

rewards.name: Tempered Trancehide

name: Zinogre
description: Lightning courses through the fur and unique plating of this fanged wyvern. It is most deadly in its supercharged state.

rewards.description: A coin given to those who have bested a Zinogre in the master rank Arena.
